                            SECTION 1. INTRODUCTION



          This document describes the procedures and parameters
          required for configuring the ALC-CMT (Character Mode
          Translator) interface.

          The ALC-CMT is a terminal interface which works in
          conjunction with an ALC-HIF (Host Interface) to enable data
          communications between asynchronous terminals and
          synchronous hosts via the Tymnet network.


          Its primary functions are:

               o  Async/ALC protocol conversion

               o  Address assignment for async sessions

               o  Session switching

               o  Emulation of an async host for async terminals

               o  Emulation of a group of synchronous TCUs for a sync
                  host

          The basic ALC-CMT configuration is described in the
          Overview, Section 2 of this manual.  Sections 3 and 4
          contain descriptions of each of the macros used, along with
          the parameters necessary to produce a complete
          configuration.  The Appendix is a sample tymfile taken from
          an actual configuration.  It may be used as a model in
          configuring an ALC-CMT interface.
