          3.1.1.  The SETTRM Macro
          ________________________

          This macro defines the allowable terminal types.  It must be
          called before the USER calls and it can have between one and
          eight parameters.

          The format for the SETTRM macro is:

               SETTRM(terminal type<s>)

          where:

               terminal type<s> can be one or any number of the
               ________________
                         following:

                    TTY52  = DEC VT52 Terminal
                    TTY78  = Protocol PCI 78
                    TTY440 = Tymshare 440 CRT (ADM-2) in block mode
                    TTY430 = Tymshare 430
                    TTY315 = Hard Copy
                    TTY470 = Tymshare 470 CRT (Super Owl 1250) in
                             block mode
                    TTY415 = Scanset
                    TTY102 = Tymshare 102 (UT102)
                    TTY431 = Tymshare 431 (ADM-11)

               When more than one terminal type is being defined with
               this macro they must be separated by commas as
               individual parameters.  For example;
               (TTY52,TTY78,TTY102)

