
          3.1.2.  The USER Macro
          ______________________

          This macro defines the username parameters for the circuits
          to be built from the terminals to the ALC-CMT.  User names
          can be defined either as global or standard.  Global
          usernames are capable of multiple simultaneous logins while
          standard usernames may have multiple simultaneous logins
          only when they are defined with multiple AGENT IDs.

          The only difference in defining a global username from a
          standard username is that for the global username, the
          'pointer to agent chain' parameter points to the GLUSER
          macro rather than pointing to the AGENT macro which it does
          for standard usernames.

          One user macro must be defined for each circuit to be built.

          The format of the USER macro is:

             USER(username,industry code,printer type,terminal
                  type,user type,license,pointer to agent
                  chain,pointer to agcres chain,entry address of ipt)

          where:

             username (maximum 12 alphanumeric characters) defines the
             ________
                  username associated with the terminal when it's
                  logged in.  If preceded by a '!', this username is
                  allowed to log in when MATS is shut.

             industry code (maximum 7 numeric characters) is used for
             _____________
                  PNR identification and in printer messages.

             printer type identifies the printer type for printers
             ____________
                  attached to CRTs:

                    PTYNOP = no printer
                    PTY736 = Tymshare 736 printer
                    PTYTGR = Flying Tigers printer

             terminal type identifies the terminal type.  Possible
             _____________
                  terminal types for the normal user:

                   LUD52  = DEC VT52 Terminal
                   LUD78  = Protocol PCI 78
                   LUD440 = Tymshare 440 CRT (ADM-2) in block mode
                   LUD430 = Tymshare 430
                   LUD315 = Hard Copy
                   LUD470 = Tymshare 470 CRT (Super Owl 1250) in block
                            mode
                   LUD415 = Scanset
                   LUD102 = Tymshare 102 (UT102)
                   LUD431 = Tymshare 431 (ADM-11)



          April 22, 1987             - 5 -                    ALCC.GEN




          ALCC SYS GEN                                   3. LUD MACROS




             More than one terminal type can be specified by adding
             them together.  For instance:

               LUD315+LUD470+LUD440

             allows three terminal types.

             user type identifies the type of user.  Possible user
             _________
             types include:

                    LUDNUR = normal user
                    LUDMUR = monitor user
                    LUDRUR = res user
                    LUDPUR = programmer user (debugging, testing)

          license specifies whether the user will be allowed to enter
          _______
          (and leave) a mode where every command bypasses the common
          language translation:

               LUDCRL      = user selectable bypass mode is allowed
               CARLOF or 0 = user selectable bypass mode is not
                             allowed

          pointer to agent chain is the label for the agent chain when
          ______________________
                        defining standard usernames, and the label for
                        the GLUSER macro when defining global
                        usernames (see section 3.1.7.)   This
                        parameter is a maximum of six alphanumeric
