          3.1.3.  The SETRES Macro
          ________________________

          This macro defines the symbol for a res number used in a
          circuit from an ALC-HIF.  It must be called once for each
          res number.  It must be called before the MAGPROMPT, SETMAG,
          AGCRES, AIDRES, and POOL calls.  There is one call per res
          symbol defintion.

          The format for this macro is:

               SETRES(res symbol,res number)

          where:

               res symbol is the res symbol res.xx
               __________

               res number is the res number in decimal used in a
               __________
                          circuit from an ALC-HIF.  RES number can be
                          any digit from 0-127 but should be defined
                          in numerical order beginning with 0.
