          3.1.7.  The AGENT/GLUSER Macro
          ______________________________

          The AGENT macro supplies data necessary to define one agent
          identifier.  There may be multiple agencies defined for a
          single username in order to allow multiple simultaneous
          logins.  The first  agent definition for an agency is
          pointed to by the USER macro.  The AGENT macro has a chain
          pointer to another AGENT macro; this chain defines all the
          agents within an agency.  Agent chains may be shared by
          agencies (usernames) which have the same agent ids and
          AIDRES values.

          The GLUSER macro has one parameter which supplies a single
          agent identifier.  It is used in place of the AGENT macro
          for defining global usernames.  The GLUSER macro defines
          global usernames which are capable of multiple simultaneous
          logins without having configured AGENT IDs.


          The format of the AGENT macro is:

               AGENT(agent initials,pointer to next agent in chain,
                         pointer to aidres chain)

          where:

               agent initials are a two character field identifying
               ______________
                         the agent.  For a given user, the agent
                         identifier has to be entered after log-on.

               pointer to next agent in chain is the (assembly label)
               ______________________________
                         name pointing to the next agent in the chain;
                         zero indicates end of chain.

               pointer to aidres chain is the label of the AIDRES
               _______________________
                         chain which contains res information for that
                         agent.



          The format of the GLUSER macro is:

               GLUSER(pointer to aidres chain)

          where:

               pointer to aidres chain is the label of the AIDRES
               _______________________
                         chain which contains res information for that
                         agent.


