          3.2.  ADDRESS MACROS
          ____________________

          The ADDRESS macros may be used to define either address
          pools or individual dedicated addresses.  An address pool is
          a set of addresses which are assigned to users on a first
          come, first served basis, while a dedicated address is
          assigned to one user and not used for login from any other
          username.



          3.2.1.  The POOL Macro
          ______________________

          The POOL macro starts an IA-TA pool definition and must be
          executed at the beginning of each pool.  There may be more
          than one pool for a particular res.

          The format of the POOL macro is:

               POOL(res number)

          where:

               res number is a decimal number expressed by a constant
               __________
                         of the form res.xy where xy is the res code
                         (e.g., res.tw,etc.)



          3.2.2.  The PIATAS Macro
          ________________________

          The PIATAS macro defines one CRT and printer IA-TA pair.
          This macro can appear only after a POOL macro, another
          PIATAS macro or a CIATAS macro.

          The format of the PIATAS macro is:

               PIATAS(crt ia-ta number,printer ia-ta number)

          where:

               crt ia-ta number defines the CRT IA-TA number
               ________________
                must be in hex.

               printer ia-ta number defines the printer IA-TA number
               ____________________
                must be in hex.

          The two parameters are logically related by ALC-CMT for
          printing operations.







          April 22, 1987             - 14 -                   ALCC.GEN




          ALCC SYS GEN                                   3. LUD MACROS


