
          3.3.1.  AUTO SIGN-IN,SIGN-OFF MACROS
          ____________________________________


          The Auto Sign-In and Auto Sign-Off features are flexible and
          fully configurable.  They share a common set of
          command/response macros which define the SC strings to be
          exchanged between the ALC-CMT and the host.  Command and
          Response strings may consist of up to 255 ASCII characters
          and may include the use of wild characters.

          Each RES has one 'Sign Command Group' which may consist of
          one or more 'Command Sets'.  A Sign Command Group defines
          the entire set of command/response macros for a RES, where a
          Command Set defines individual command/response macro
          sequences.  Both a Sign Command Group and a Command Set
          begin with a SGNBEG macro and end with a SGNEND macro.  The
          difference between them is that a Sign Command Group must be
          ended with the SGNEND macro followed by the ENDGRP
          parameter; SGNEND(ENDGRP), and a Commamd Set is ended with
          the SGNEND macro followed by the ENDSET parameter;
          SGNEND(ENDSET).

          Diagram 1.A illustrates the relationship between a Command
          Set and a Sign Command Group.



                               SIGN COMMAND GROUP
                               __________________


               SGNBEG
                   SGNCMD(CMD1)
                   SGNRSP(RSP1,RSPDNE)
                   SGNRSP(RSP2)
                                          ---------->COMMAND SET
                   SGNCMD(CMD2)
                   SGNRSP(RSP1)
                   SGNRSP(RSP2)
                   SGNRSP(RSP3)
               SGNEND(ENDSET)

               SGNBEG
                   SGNCMD(CMD1)           ---------->COMMAND SET
                   SGNRSP(RSP1)
               SGNEND(ENDGRP)
