          DEFDEF(SGOTIM,$A RATE * 15)

          Default response timeout value.   If no response is received
          to a sign-off in SGOTIM amount of time, it will be
          considered a 'NO RESPONSE' from the host.


          DEFDEF(SGOLMT,$A 3)

          Maximum number of retries for the first sign-off attempt.
          This is the number of times that the ALC-CMT will attempt to
          sign-off a host before freezing the address.
