          3.3.2.  The STAHST Macro
          ________________________

          The STAHST macro defines circuits to be built from the ALC-
          CMT to an ASCII host running an optional statistics
          gathering program.  One STAHST macro must be defined for
          each circuit to be built.

          The format of the STAHST macro is:

               STAHST(username,host number,status,ordinal,password)

          where:

               username is the username used when the circuit is built
               ________
                         to the host.

               host number identifies the host to which this circuit
               ___________
                         is being built.

               status indicates the status of the host.  The two
               ______
                         options allowed are:

                    HSON - circuits may be built to this host
                    HSOFF - circuits may not be built to this host

               ordinal is the order in which the circuit building
               _______
                       attempt should be made by the ALC-CMT.  Must be
                       >=1.  The host with the ordinal equal to 1 will
                       have the highest circuit building priority.

               password is the password in the login string used to
               ________
                         get into the host for statistics gathering
                         and reporting.
