
          3.3.5.  The PJCODE Macro
          ________________________

          The PJCODE macro is used to enable or disable the Project
          Code feature for an ALC-CMT user.  When this feature is
          enabled the user will type in project code as a part of
          his/her login.  For example - username; password;project
          code <cr>.  The project code information is then sent to the
          network supervisor and included in the customer's accounting
          data.

          The Project Code field may consist of up to 25 characters
          minus the number of characters in the login username.  When
          ALC-CMT is configured with the Project Code option, the ALCC
          has a default 'wait' time of 3 seconds.  This indicates the
          amount of time the ALC-CMT will wait for a project code to
          be entered by the user after the username login sequence.
          If project code is not entered within the specified 'wait'
          time, project code data entered after that time will still
          be sent to the supervisor but will not be retained by the
          ALC-CMT.

          The format of the PJCODE macro is:

               PJCODE(ENABLE/DISABLE)

          where:

               enable enables the Project Code feature.
               ______

               disable disables the Project Code feature.
               _______



          In order to configure a 'wait' time other than 3 seconds
          place the following variable equation after the PJCODE
          macro.

               DEFDEF(WATPJC,$A rate * value)

          where:

               $A indicates that the following value will be in hex.
               __

               rate equals 600 TICKS or 1 second.
               ____

               value is the hex value for this equation.
               _____


